33
00:01:10,583 --> 00:01:12,333
Well, I think you were
totally dazzling.

34
00:01:12,416 --> 00:01:14,208
-[gasps] Really?!
-Mm-hmm.

35
00:01:14,291 --> 00:01:15,875
[giggles]

36
00:01:15,958 --> 00:01:17,291
[SAKURA] You have the kind
of smile that lights up a room!

37
00:01:17,375 --> 00:01:20,000
-And that star is so cute!
-Thank you!

38
00:01:21,916 --> 00:01:24,166
Amamoto,
what's your lunch order?

39
00:01:25,291 --> 00:01:26,750
[AMAMOTO]
Sicilian rice bowl.

40
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:28,750
Yup. Shoulda guessed.

41
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:32,291
-How ‘bout you?
-Nothing for me.

42
00:01:32,375 --> 00:01:34,375
-[ROOKIE] Okay.
-[TAKEO] Be back soon.

43
00:01:34,458 --> 00:01:35,916
Sure.

44
00:01:37,166 --> 00:01:39,875
Does Go leave for lunch
every day or what?

45
00:01:39,958 --> 00:01:41,625
It's because he hates TV.

46
00:01:41,708 --> 00:01:44,958
Ah, seems like a lot of people
have moved past it, huh?

47
00:01:45,041 --> 00:01:46,666
That's not exactly why,

48
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:48,875
-but yeah.
-[ROOKIE] Eh?

49
00:01:55,125 --> 00:01:56,833
[chomps]

50
00:02:00,708 --> 00:02:02,625
Uh...

51
00:02:02,708 --> 00:02:06,500
Huh-- mm.

52
00:02:06,583 --> 00:02:09,625
[MOTHER] Sweetheart,
what are you doing?

53
00:02:09,708 --> 00:02:11,333
Huh?

54
00:02:11,416 --> 00:02:14,750
-Come along, now.
-[GIRL sighs]

55
00:02:22,291 --> 00:02:24,916
[shocked gasp]

56
00:03:54,916 --> 00:03:58,333
[blowing shell, badly]

57
00:03:58,416 --> 00:04:00,333
[TAE snoring]

58
00:04:00,416 --> 00:04:02,625
Good morning!

59
00:04:02,708 --> 00:04:05,708
-[SAKURA] Good morning, sir!
-[JUNKO] It's nice to see you.

60
00:04:05,791 --> 00:04:07,916
Well, ladies,
congrats on the great press!

61
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,500
[ALL giggle]

62
00:04:09,583 --> 00:04:11,083
So, Junko.

63
00:04:11,166 --> 00:04:13,041
What were your thoughts
about the Saga Rock Festival?

64
00:04:13,125 --> 00:04:15,291
Oh... um...

65
00:04:15,375 --> 00:04:17,750
it shows we have potential,
you know?

66
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:19,958
Yeah!
That's what I thought!

67
00:04:20,041 --> 00:04:22,791
You're riding on
a wave of popularity!

68
00:04:22,875 --> 00:04:24,916
[SAKURA]
She seems better.

69
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,458
And how about you?

70
00:04:26,541 --> 00:04:30,500
-Are you enjoying the ride?
-Me? I dunno. I, uh...

71
00:04:30,583 --> 00:04:32,125
Are you gonna say
don't get cocky--

72
00:04:32,208 --> 00:04:34,083
Do get cocky!

73
00:04:34,166 --> 00:04:36,208
You're in a magazine, aren't ya?

74
00:04:36,291 --> 00:04:38,250
Stick out that Pinocchio nose,

75
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:39,750
if you're gonna ride
this hype wave!

76
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:42,208
[chuckling]
Surf, bro.

77
00:04:42,291 --> 00:04:44,083
Uh...

78
00:04:44,166 --> 00:04:45,833
[KOTARO]
How do you like it, Lily?

79
00:04:45,916 --> 00:04:48,250
Is that star thingy
on your skull getting bigger?

80
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:49,958
No, that's dumb!

81
00:04:50,041 --> 00:04:52,916
-[LILY whimpering]
-Aw, what's the matter, kiddo?

82
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,125
What did I do?

83
00:04:54,208 --> 00:04:55,875
Hurt your fee-fees?

84
00:04:55,958 --> 00:04:58,833
Is your star gonna get all big
like the rocks at Kyoseki Park?

85
00:04:58,916 --> 00:05:00,291
That'd be cool, right?

86
00:05:00,375 --> 00:05:01,416
-[KOTARO] Come on!
-Jeez, you're so damn creepy!

87
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:03,208
[LILY whimpers]

88
00:05:05,375 --> 00:05:06,333
Tee-hee!

89
00:05:06,416 --> 00:05:07,375
Anyway!

90
00:05:07,458 --> 00:05:09,083
If we want a real fan uprising,

91
00:05:09,166 --> 00:05:11,083
we'll need to use every
advantage we can rustle up!

92
00:05:12,375 --> 00:05:13,666
Soon we'll be a household name

93
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:15,833
that every man, woman,
and child in Saga knows!

94
00:05:15,916 --> 00:05:18,416
Pop-up shows, meetups, TV spots.

95
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:21,208
If there's an eyeball open,
I want you in it.

96
00:05:21,291 --> 00:05:23,666
Let's have a good
old-fashioned zombie outbreak!

97
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:25,500
[blows seashell, badly]

98
00:05:25,583 --> 00:05:28,750
♪

99
00:05:48,125 --> 00:05:51,083
Who's ready for a photo-op
with your favorite idol, huh?

100
00:05:51,166 --> 00:05:52,666
By the way,

101
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:55,375
you can also get a signed
glamour shot from Number Four.

102
00:05:55,458 --> 00:05:57,041
[crowd chatter]

103
00:05:57,125 --> 00:05:59,541
And please remember that
touching is prohibited.

104
00:05:59,625 --> 00:06:00,708
Don't be creepy.

105
00:06:03,916 --> 00:06:06,791
[camera whirring, printing]

106
00:06:06,875 --> 00:06:08,833
[LILY giggles]

107
00:06:10,416 --> 00:06:13,166
Don't look now,
but we've got trouble.

108
00:06:13,250 --> 00:06:16,583
What happened?
Whoa, he's giant!

109
00:06:16,666 --> 00:06:19,333
Yeah, that guy's Yakuza,
no doubt about it.

110
00:06:19,416 --> 00:06:20,541
You think?

111
00:06:20,625 --> 00:06:22,666
[SAKI]
Maybe Shades got in some trouble

112
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,666
and he's here to collect.

113
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:26,708
That sounds bad!

114
00:06:26,791 --> 00:06:27,958
Wait, where's Mr. Kotaro?

115
00:06:28,041 --> 00:06:30,333
[SAKI]
He musta run for the hills!

116
00:06:30,416 --> 00:06:32,083
[SAKURA gasps]
Uh...

117
00:06:32,166 --> 00:06:34,625
[SAKURA] Looks like he
wants to get a photo.

118
00:06:34,708 --> 00:06:35,708
[SAKI and SAKURA]
Huh?

119
00:06:35,791 --> 00:06:38,416
[SAKI]
He's here for the runt?

120
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:40,375
[SAKURA]
Guess he's a fan of Lily's.

121
00:06:40,458 --> 00:06:42,541
I wouldn't let my guard down
just yet.

122
00:06:42,625 --> 00:06:44,500
If we're big enough
to be in Sagazine,

123
00:06:44,583 --> 00:06:46,375
then there's gonna be
a few weirdos.

124
00:06:46,458 --> 00:06:48,416
[SAKI]
For all we know,

125
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:50,500
he came here
to kidnap the little squirt!

126
00:06:50,583 --> 00:06:51,666
[SAKURA]
Oh, God!

127
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,875
[MALE FAN]
Your show was so amazing!

128
00:06:53,958 --> 00:06:56,208
-I'll come again!
-Thanks a lot!

129
00:06:56,291 --> 00:06:57,750
[giggles]
Bye-bye!

130
00:06:57,833 --> 00:07:00,000
Nice to meet you.
I'm Number Six!

131
00:07:00,083 --> 00:07:01,541
Uh...

132
00:07:01,625 --> 00:07:04,666
You... you're really...

133
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,541
Hell no, I don't
think so, buddy!

134
00:07:09,625 --> 00:07:12,666
[SAKI yelling]

135
00:07:14,083 --> 00:07:15,583
[TAKEO grunts]

136
00:07:15,666 --> 00:07:17,291
-Ow!
-[thud]

137
00:07:18,541 --> 00:07:19,541
[SAKI scoffs]

138
00:07:19,625 --> 00:07:21,458
[indistinct crowd chatter]

139
00:07:21,541 --> 00:07:22,958
Uh...

140
00:07:23,041 --> 00:07:25,208
Uh, let's step back, okay?

141
00:07:25,291 --> 00:07:27,041
-But, wait...
-[FAN 1] What just happened?

142
00:07:27,125 --> 00:07:28,958
-that was my--
-[FAN 2] Holy crap.

143
00:07:29,041 --> 00:07:30,458
[FAN 3]
A rolling sobat!

144
00:07:30,541 --> 00:07:31,958
-She gave me a fright!
-[KOTARO] Sorry about that,

145
00:07:32,041 --> 00:07:33,666
-I nearly wet me knickers!
-Folks, no need to worry!

146
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:35,958
Yeah, that Number Two
girl's hardcore!

147
00:07:36,041 --> 00:07:38,250
-That guy's lucky.
-Hmm?

148
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:41,666
[KOTARO singing]
Oh yeah, oh yeah, oh yay-uh!

149
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:44,000
Oh yeah,
oh yeah, oh yay-uh!

150
00:07:44,083 --> 00:07:46,583
-Oh--
-[JUNKO] Excuse me!

151
00:07:46,666 --> 00:07:48,083
Um, there's trouble!

152
00:07:50,625 --> 00:07:53,375
[growling]

153
00:07:53,458 --> 00:07:56,500
We told ya, no touchin'
the talent! Got that?

154
00:07:56,583 --> 00:07:59,583
I'm sorry, it's just...

155
00:07:59,666 --> 00:08:01,000
that girl looks like--

156
00:08:01,083 --> 00:08:03,208
[SAKI]
Spit it out, would ya?

157
00:08:03,291 --> 00:08:06,916
[TAKEO] Seven years ago, there
was this famous child TV actor

158
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,833
by the name of Lily Hoshikawa.

159
00:08:08,916 --> 00:08:11,000
[ALL gasp]

160
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:21,750
What happened to Lily,
could happen to any of us.

161
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:23,791
-Especially to Junko and me.
-You're right.

162
00:08:23,875 --> 00:08:27,250
We don't use names,
but people know our faces.

163
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:30,666
I'm afraid that being a public
figure is quite dangerous,

164
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:32,416
more so now than ever.

165
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:34,000
Ughh!

166
00:08:34,083 --> 00:08:36,500
This is such a freakin' drag!

167
00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:38,458
Hang on.

168
00:08:38,541 --> 00:08:41,166
Don't ya think Lily should
be done washing up by now?

169
00:08:45,041 --> 00:08:46,500
[LILY gasps]

170
00:08:46,583 --> 00:08:50,041
I didn't see you next
to the faucet, so I got worried.

171
00:08:50,125 --> 00:08:51,375
Wanna talk?

172
00:08:52,583 --> 00:08:54,083
Look, Sakura.

173
00:08:54,166 --> 00:08:56,875
That guy from before...

174
00:08:56,958 --> 00:08:59,500
well, see, he was
actually my Papa.

175
00:08:59,583 --> 00:09:02,666
Huh? Your dad's... Yakuza?

176
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:03,750
He's what?

177
00:09:03,833 --> 00:09:05,791
No way! He was enormous!

178
00:09:05,875 --> 00:09:08,041
Well, I take after my Mama.

179
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:11,083
I didn't think
he would ever show up

180
00:09:11,166 --> 00:09:12,416
at one of our fan events.

181
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:14,541
Must be weird.

182
00:09:15,583 --> 00:09:16,958
Honestly?

183
00:09:17,041 --> 00:09:20,208
I've been trying my hardest
to forget about him.

184
00:09:20,291 --> 00:09:22,000
But now I can't.

185
00:09:24,333 --> 00:09:26,833
[LILY] It was usually
just the two of us.

186
00:09:26,916 --> 00:09:29,750
But still, I was never lonely.

187
00:09:29,833 --> 00:09:33,458
I knew that Mama was watching
over us from up in the sky.

188
00:09:33,541 --> 00:09:36,625
And we had a TV set, too!

189
00:09:36,708 --> 00:09:38,458
Papa's favorite thing to do

190
00:09:38,541 --> 00:09:40,916
was relax in front
of the TV together.

191
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,041
He used to say,

192
00:09:42,125 --> 00:09:43,791
"No matter how good
a show was,

193
00:09:43,875 --> 00:09:45,416
"it was even better
if you could laugh and cry

194
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:48,291
along with another person
while you watch."

195
00:09:48,375 --> 00:09:51,500
He'd always want me to sit
next to him on the couch.

196
00:09:51,583 --> 00:09:54,541
Even if I had homework.

197
00:09:54,625 --> 00:09:59,041
Seeing how much he enjoyed TV
made me really happy.

198
00:09:59,125 --> 00:10:00,833
So I thought it'd be nice

199
00:10:00,916 --> 00:10:03,958
if I could make him smile
from inside the TV!

200
00:10:04,041 --> 00:10:06,833
I signed with
a children's talent agency,

201
00:10:06,916 --> 00:10:09,750
and then he quit his job
so he could be my manager.

202
00:10:09,833 --> 00:10:13,166
Whenever I had work,
Papa was right there with me.

203
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:16,833
And of course, I was adorable
and talented from the get-go,

204
00:10:16,916 --> 00:10:18,125
so every show I was a part of

205
00:10:18,208 --> 00:10:20,125
turned into a big hit
automatically!

206
00:10:20,208 --> 00:10:22,583
Uh... but...

207
00:10:22,666 --> 00:10:24,166
as soon as I made it
to the top,

208
00:10:24,250 --> 00:10:26,958
something real bad
happened to me.

209
00:10:30,333 --> 00:10:31,708
[knocking at door]

210
00:10:31,791 --> 00:10:33,416
[TAKEO]
Open the door, Masao!

211
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,375
They can't get the show
moving without you!

212
00:10:35,458 --> 00:10:37,333
I'm not going anywhere!

213
00:10:37,416 --> 00:10:40,416
Don't worry!
They can edit that part out!

214
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:43,833
All that matters to you
is the me that's on the screen!

215
00:10:43,916 --> 00:10:46,583
[LILY] You don't care
about the real me!

216
00:10:46,666 --> 00:10:48,500
You know that's not true!

217
00:10:48,583 --> 00:10:50,083
It's just some leg hair.

218
00:10:50,166 --> 00:10:53,458
[TAKEO] It means you're
growing up, that's all.

219
00:10:53,541 --> 00:10:56,208
No, I'm never growing up!
Hmm!

220
00:10:58,625 --> 00:11:01,083
You can't look
that way forever, you know.

221
00:11:01,166 --> 00:11:03,666
Yes I can, and I'm going to!

222
00:11:03,750 --> 00:11:05,333
I don't want to
look like you, Papa!

223
00:11:05,416 --> 00:11:07,875
[LILY]
Leave me alone!

224
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:10,583
Masao!
This is your job!

225
00:11:10,666 --> 00:11:13,125
Lots of people are excited
for this show!

226
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:15,375
-Now, come out!
-[pounding on door]

227
00:11:16,916 --> 00:11:19,916
I'll always be just like this.

228
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:23,083
Do I have some food
stuck on my face?

229
00:11:27,291 --> 00:11:30,416
-[tugging at hair]
-[rip]

230
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:33,541
[stammering]

231
00:11:33,625 --> 00:11:36,958
A-a-a hair!

232
00:11:37,041 --> 00:11:38,041
Huh--

233
00:11:38,125 --> 00:11:41,708
♪

234
00:11:41,791 --> 00:11:45,375
That's enough!
I'm comin' in!

235
00:11:45,458 --> 00:11:48,375
[grunts]

236
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:50,583
[gasps, stammers]

237
00:11:56,666 --> 00:11:59,125
Please, wake up.

238
00:11:59,208 --> 00:12:01,875
Masao!

239
00:12:01,958 --> 00:12:04,583
And that was the last time
I saw Papa.

240
00:12:04,666 --> 00:12:08,791
Um, wait.
So, what happened?

241
00:12:08,875 --> 00:12:11,916
Sorry, it was kinda hard
to keep up.

242
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:14,625
Who's this Masao guy
you were talking about?

243
00:12:14,708 --> 00:12:17,916
It's what my name
used to be.

244
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:21,958
Oh... what?!

245
00:12:31,916 --> 00:12:34,833
There you have it,
Lily used to be Masao.

246
00:12:34,916 --> 00:12:36,333
[SAKI snickering]

247
00:12:36,416 --> 00:12:38,125
I mostly can't believe
you dropped dead

248
00:12:38,208 --> 00:12:39,250
over a dumb whisker!

249
00:12:39,333 --> 00:12:40,791
How lame is that?

250
00:12:40,875 --> 00:12:42,250
-[SAKI laughs]
-Saki!

251
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:45,958
Wait, so you had a totally
different name, right?

252
00:12:46,041 --> 00:12:47,833
Yeah, Masao Go.

253
00:12:47,916 --> 00:12:50,916
[laughing]
That's so crazy.

254
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:53,333
All this time,
and we still had no idea!

255
00:12:53,416 --> 00:12:54,583
Tell us your dad's name, too!

256
00:12:54,666 --> 00:12:56,458
It's Takeo Go.

257
00:12:56,541 --> 00:12:58,250
[laughing uncontrollably]

258
00:12:58,333 --> 00:13:00,750
They're such manly names!

259
00:13:00,833 --> 00:13:03,708
Stop being a jerk!

260
00:13:03,791 --> 00:13:06,916
I'm not laughin' at you,
it's just too perfect!

261
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:09,208
Well, this is unexpected.

262
00:13:09,291 --> 00:13:12,458
[sighs]
Okay, so what happens now?

263
00:13:12,541 --> 00:13:15,333
I'm still the same Lily,
and always will be.

264
00:13:15,416 --> 00:13:16,708
And now I won't
ever grow up!

265
00:13:16,791 --> 00:13:19,000
There's no need to worry!

266
00:13:19,083 --> 00:13:20,541
I guess not.

267
00:13:20,625 --> 00:13:23,791
Wait, so did he know this?

268
00:13:23,875 --> 00:13:25,916
-[strums guitar]
-Of course I knew about her.

269
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,875
[FRANCHOUCHOU groans]

270
00:13:27,958 --> 00:13:29,375
Ah-hee.

271
00:13:29,458 --> 00:13:31,291
I am so gonna kill you!

272
00:13:31,375 --> 00:13:32,875
What?!

273
00:13:32,958 --> 00:13:34,708
So you've got room for Lily
in your little girly club,

274
00:13:34,791 --> 00:13:35,958
but Masao's not welcome?

275
00:13:36,041 --> 00:13:37,666
I said I'm not Masao.

276
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:38,875
I'm Lily! Hmph.

277
00:13:38,958 --> 00:13:41,625
Right! She's not Masao,
she's Lily!

278
00:13:41,708 --> 00:13:43,750
You guys are Masao!
I'm Lily!

279
00:13:43,833 --> 00:13:46,500
Anyway, you've got
a big show tomorrow!

280
00:13:46,583 --> 00:13:49,000
If you have time
for tired-ass questions,

281
00:13:49,083 --> 00:13:52,166
you might as well go to bed,
ya braindead brats!

282
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:53,750
[TAE groans]

283
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:56,250
[breathing heavily]

284
00:13:56,333 --> 00:13:57,916
Aw, she's so cute.

285
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:00,375
We've been working so close
together, and we never realized.

286
00:14:00,458 --> 00:14:02,416
Who cares, why does it matter

287
00:14:02,500 --> 00:14:03,833
what kind of equipment
she's got?

288
00:14:03,916 --> 00:14:06,375
-Equip... ment? Oh.
-[SAKI] We're all dead.

289
00:14:06,458 --> 00:14:08,250
We've still got that in common.

290
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:11,958
You know. It begs the question
of what zombies are.

291
00:14:12,041 --> 00:14:13,750
To think that we'll never age.

292
00:14:13,833 --> 00:14:16,041
It's not all bad.

293
00:14:16,125 --> 00:14:17,583
Lily gets to stay young.

294
00:14:17,666 --> 00:14:19,083
And none of us
will ever change either.

295
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:21,625
It's kinda nice.

296
00:14:23,041 --> 00:14:26,125
[car passes]

297
00:14:26,208 --> 00:14:28,583
[TAKEO]
Look at this!

298
00:14:28,666 --> 00:14:31,041
We got excellent ratings!

299
00:14:31,125 --> 00:14:34,291
That means you've impressed a
lot of people with your acting!

300
00:14:34,375 --> 00:14:37,291
Today's special guest
is Miss Lily Hoshikawa.

301
00:14:37,375 --> 00:14:38,750
[LILY on TV]
Thanks for having me!

302
00:14:38,833 --> 00:14:41,541
You see that?
Wooo! You're a natural!

303
00:14:41,625 --> 00:14:43,708
-Keep it up!
-Papa?

304
00:14:43,791 --> 00:14:46,833
Aw! They missed that adorable
look you gave there!

305
00:14:46,916 --> 00:14:48,833
Hey, I was wondering
if the two of us

306
00:14:48,916 --> 00:14:50,041
could go somewhere together.

307
00:14:50,125 --> 00:14:51,791
Where's that, dear?

308
00:14:51,875 --> 00:14:54,375
I want to go back to Kouno Park.

309
00:14:54,458 --> 00:14:55,541
Just you and me.

310
00:14:55,625 --> 00:14:57,000
Sure...

311
00:14:57,083 --> 00:14:58,916
Yeah, as soon as filming
for this show is finished.

312
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,333
[disappointed]
Mm...

313
00:15:01,416 --> 00:15:03,125
Yep! He's the best!

314
00:15:05,541 --> 00:15:08,541
We think it was caused
by a mental shock.

315
00:15:08,625 --> 00:15:10,250
To die from that,

316
00:15:10,333 --> 00:15:13,708
the brain must've been under
great distress before the fall.

317
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:18,833
[LILY'S voice]
Papa!

318
00:15:23,083 --> 00:15:27,666
[crying]

319
00:15:30,416 --> 00:15:31,750
It's just too painful!

320
00:15:34,250 --> 00:15:35,500
[grunts]

321
00:15:35,583 --> 00:15:38,458
[screaming]

322
00:15:38,541 --> 00:15:41,416
[TV crashes to the floor]

323
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:44,500
[panting]

324
00:15:46,416 --> 00:15:48,833
Get a grip.

325
00:15:48,916 --> 00:15:51,041
That girl's not Masao.

326
00:15:51,125 --> 00:15:53,875
She couldn't be.

327
00:15:53,958 --> 00:15:56,791
[indistinct crowd chatter]

328
00:16:01,916 --> 00:16:04,666
Hi again!
Sorry about last time.

329
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:06,500
Number Two
didn't mean you any harm.

330
00:16:06,583 --> 00:16:09,333
No. It was totally my fault.

331
00:16:09,416 --> 00:16:11,250
So, uh,
could I get a T-shirt?

332
00:16:11,333 --> 00:16:13,583
Mm-hmm, I don't think
it'll fit you, though,

333
00:16:13,666 --> 00:16:14,875
you wear a five-X.

334
00:16:14,958 --> 00:16:16,375
How'd you know that?

335
00:16:16,458 --> 00:16:17,875
[gasps]

336
00:16:17,958 --> 00:16:20,708
Well, we meet a lot of fans,
so it's easy to guess!

337
00:16:20,791 --> 00:16:22,083
I see.

338
00:16:22,166 --> 00:16:24,041
In that case,
an extra-small.

339
00:16:24,125 --> 00:16:25,333
Huh?

340
00:16:25,416 --> 00:16:26,583
[TAKEO]
You see...

341
00:16:26,666 --> 00:16:28,958
I used to have a kid
about your age.

342
00:16:29,041 --> 00:16:32,583
But, uh. I wasn't
what you'd call the best dad.

343
00:16:32,666 --> 00:16:35,000
I was so focused on myself,

344
00:16:35,083 --> 00:16:37,791
I couldn't care
for my child properly.

345
00:16:37,875 --> 00:16:40,250
I hope that your father
is a nice man.

346
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:41,500
Mm-hmm!

347
00:16:41,583 --> 00:16:44,166
Pa-- uh, I mean,
my father's really great!

348
00:16:44,250 --> 00:16:46,291
He's the sweetest
and kindest ever!

349
00:16:49,833 --> 00:16:51,083
Thanks a lot.

350
00:16:51,166 --> 00:16:53,083
And I'm sorry
for frightening you before.

351
00:16:53,166 --> 00:16:54,291
I won't bother you again.

352
00:16:54,375 --> 00:16:55,333
[gasps]

353
00:16:55,416 --> 00:16:58,208
I'm just here...
to apologize.

354
00:17:00,375 --> 00:17:01,750
Goodbye.

355
00:17:01,833 --> 00:17:02,916
Uh...

356
00:17:08,041 --> 00:17:09,416
You okay?

357
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:11,916
Yeah, totally,
why wouldn't I be?

358
00:17:15,083 --> 00:17:17,125
-[door opens]
-[LILY] Mm?

359
00:17:17,208 --> 00:17:20,000
I guess we should
get to practice, huh?

360
00:17:20,083 --> 00:17:21,791
It's cool.

361
00:17:21,875 --> 00:17:24,041
We were thinking you might need
a little more time to yourself.

362
00:17:24,125 --> 00:17:25,791
You know what?

363
00:17:25,875 --> 00:17:27,875
I betcha I'd be better off
if I was like you

364
00:17:27,958 --> 00:17:30,000
and didn't have any memories.

365
00:17:30,083 --> 00:17:31,250
No way.

366
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:33,833
It's great you and your dad
met again.

367
00:17:33,916 --> 00:17:36,208
I mean, if you didn't remember
each other then...

368
00:17:36,291 --> 00:17:39,500
you wouldn't understand
your feelings.

369
00:17:39,583 --> 00:17:40,916
Papa.

370
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,166
I've been gone so long,
but he still loves me.

371
00:17:44,291 --> 00:17:46,666
And I...

372
00:17:46,750 --> 00:17:48,375
I still...

373
00:17:48,458 --> 00:17:51,708
[sobbing]

374
00:17:58,708 --> 00:18:00,666
[SAKI]
That kinda makes me think.

375
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:03,375
People must be busted up
over us, too.

376
00:18:03,458 --> 00:18:06,333
[SAKURA] I can't figure out
what this familiar feeling is.

377
00:18:06,416 --> 00:18:10,708
I can kinda remember
a single memory...

378
00:18:10,791 --> 00:18:13,625
but where and when was it?

379
00:18:13,708 --> 00:18:16,000
You all right?

380
00:18:16,083 --> 00:18:17,291
Oh! Yeah, I'm fine!

381
00:18:17,375 --> 00:18:18,583
[sighs]

382
00:18:18,666 --> 00:18:20,750
Look., we gotta do
somethin', and quick.

383
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:24,000
What can we do?
I'm a zombie now.

384
00:18:24,083 --> 00:18:27,125
Don't give up yet, we just have
to put our heads together.

385
00:18:27,208 --> 00:18:28,458
We'll find a way.

386
00:18:28,541 --> 00:18:29,750
Thanks, Sakura.

387
00:18:29,833 --> 00:18:31,166
[AI]
I think the answer's clear.

388
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:32,375
[BOTH]
Huh?

389
00:18:32,458 --> 00:18:34,166
Yeah, and it happens
to be something

390
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:36,166
that only Franchouchou can do.

391
00:18:36,250 --> 00:18:38,625
But first,
we need to ask Kotaro.

392
00:18:38,708 --> 00:18:42,666
[piano playing]

393
00:18:51,416 --> 00:18:53,583
[ROOKIE]
Oh, I almost forgot,

394
00:18:53,666 --> 00:18:56,500
that came in the mail.

395
00:18:56,583 --> 00:18:59,000
I'll just throw it out.

396
00:18:59,083 --> 00:19:01,291
Man, it must be next
to impossible for local idols

397
00:19:01,375 --> 00:19:03,916
to get popular these days.

398
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:05,916
[ROOKIE imitates shooting gun]

399
00:19:08,125 --> 00:19:11,083
[crowd cheering]

400
00:19:11,166 --> 00:19:12,750
Uh... uh...

401
00:19:15,375 --> 00:19:19,000
The show's almost over.
Think he'll be here?

402
00:19:19,083 --> 00:19:21,750
-We've done all that we can.
-Hmm...

403
00:19:23,541 --> 00:19:24,875
-[heavy footsteps]
-[gasps]

404
00:19:24,958 --> 00:19:27,708
[PAPA panting]

405
00:19:36,166 --> 00:19:37,708
Papa!

406
00:19:37,791 --> 00:19:42,500
Hey! Guess what?
We got a new song!

407
00:19:42,583 --> 00:19:45,166
And the squirt's gonna be
the lead singer!

408
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:46,916
Saki, you can't call her that!

409
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:49,041
Uh. Right, I mean Number Six!

410
00:19:49,125 --> 00:19:50,875
[CROWD cheering]

411
00:19:53,791 --> 00:19:57,541
Here's our new song,
called "To My Dearest."

412
00:21:06,166 --> 00:21:08,666
I'm really happy that you
came out here to see our show.

413
00:21:08,750 --> 00:21:12,041
I've always had a passion
for TV, though.

414
00:21:12,125 --> 00:21:14,833
That's why I'm going to work
hard to be onscreen a lot!

415
00:21:14,916 --> 00:21:17,125
And when you see me there,

416
00:21:17,208 --> 00:21:19,083
I hope it makes you smile!

417
00:21:19,166 --> 00:21:21,500
I can't tell you
how much it means to me

418
00:21:21,583 --> 00:21:23,541
to look out there and see you.

419
00:21:23,625 --> 00:21:25,583
I promise I won't forget you.

420
00:21:25,666 --> 00:21:27,791
And I love you!

421
00:22:58,458 --> 00:22:59,541
[giggles]

422
00:22:59,625 --> 00:23:02,416
Amamoto!
What's your lunch order?

423
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:07,416
-Sicilian rice bowl.
-Same freakin' thing every day.

424
00:23:07,500 --> 00:23:10,208
-Hey, one udon. Chicken.
-What?

425
00:23:10,291 --> 00:23:13,250
-So you're gonna eat here today?
-Yeah.

426
00:23:16,875 --> 00:23:18,833
These girls are so hilarious.

427
00:23:18,916 --> 00:23:22,000
Yeah, I cracked up
when I saw this.

428
00:23:33,166 --> 00:23:35,458
Saki here!
Next time, Episode 9,

429
00:23:35,541 --> 00:23:37,583
"Though My Life May Have Ended
Once by Some Twist of Fate,

430
00:23:37,666 --> 00:23:39,791
"I Have Risen, and if Song
and Dance are to be My Fate,

431
00:23:39,875 --> 00:23:41,333
"Then Carrying
the Memories of My Comrades

432
00:23:41,416 --> 00:23:44,166
in My Heart as I Sally Forth
Shall be My SAGA."

433
00:23:44,250 --> 00:23:45,208
Whew!

